The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Dec. 27: Telecom regulator Trai is likely to postpone the January deadline to bring an end to unsolicited calls and messages to February 1. In December, the Telecom Regulatory Authority of India had come out with guidelines on unsolicited telemarketing calls and text messages, to be implemented from January 1, 2011.                            
	 New Delhi, Dec. 27: The government is unlikely to hike diesel prices later this week as it will have a spiralling effect on food inflation. State-owned oil firms are losing about Rs 6 a litre at present.                             
	 Jamshedpur, Dec. 27: Tata Steel said it would infuse $500 million in its European arm in the next fiscal and asserted that the new year would see its joint venture with Japans Nippon Steel Corp bearing fruits.
                                                                                                                          
